manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Goalfish 2-Male to 2-Male RCA Audio Stereo Cable Goalfish 2RCA Male to 2RCA Male Stereo Audio Cable are good choices for home theater, HDTV, gaming consoles, hi-fi systems by amplifying sound quality for a more enjoyable audio experience. 24K Gold-plated connectors are for improved audio/video signal transfer and less signal interference. RCA is a great alternative for audio/video applications where newer connection types are not available. With its 2-Male connectors on the both ends, the cable allows for 2 RCA output (connect to either L or R input) and 2 RCA input, where the input can be high frequency (digital audio) or low frequency (subwoofer). With a subwoofer, this cables can significantly increase sound levels, without having to turn up the volume, plus it eliminates unwanted noise/feedback for pure audio. Maximize your system’s audio output with help from the user-friendly goalfish high-quality audio cable. Compatible Devices RCA ports are compatible with various kinds of stereo players(devices with red and white RCA female). -TV, DVD, Amplifier, Sound box, Car, Xbox 360, PS3, Wii, HDTV, A/V receiver, any other audio equipment etc. NOTE: Please pay attention that our cables can only be used for transmitting audio signal, not for video signal transmission. Please ensure compatibility and correct operation of all connected equipment before the cable is permanently installed inside a permanent fixture.

24K Gold-Plated Connector 24K gold-plated contacts giving you the flexibility you need for your listening pleasure.Red/black color-marked connectors for quick, easy left-and-right hookups. Durable Construction The integrated anti-stretch design does not easily cause tearing, making it safer to use.Premium metallic housing which makes it easily survive everyday usage and gives it a more stylish and elegant appearance that goes great with your expensive gadgets. Premium Sound Quality Metal shell of this stereo RCA cable provides reliable performance and reducing signal loss.Made of 99.99% OFC(Oxygen free copper), seamlessly transmits stereo audio for high quality sounds.

Long-Lasting Performance Design - Flexible Braided Cord The 2RCA to 2RCA Cable Adds the strong military fiber, the most flexible, powerful and durable material, makes tensile force increased by 200%, special strain relief support design, can bear 15000+ bending test.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Audiophile quality cables for sure!
reviews.reviewText: Took a chance after an hour of browsing, decided to grab these. Dude, am I glad I did! These are some good, good little guys! First, they're beautiful (which, with my amps showing, looks plays a big part).A little stiff when first opened, but after working them a bit, they become more flexible and super easy to run through my car.Being as thin as they are, I was a bit skeptical, but once I installed everything and fired it up, the SQ is absolutely top notch. These guys are easily worth 3 times as much.ZERO noise interference (of course if you take precaution running cables properly and getting a good ground, noise should never be an issue).Connectors are small but seat firmly and are solidly built.For the price, there's no way you could find a better cable. Grab them before the price jumps!Seller is great, arrived before expected. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value great cable
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been looking for a decent rca cable to replace all of my mismatched cables without breaking the bank. I figure for the price I'd give them a shot. They’re working out great! Anyone who deals with old tube stuff knows how close they put the rca connections to each other due to smaller cable ends. These fit perfectly without having to fight the cable ends in. The 2 into one wire is nice for routing the wire cleanly.Due to the thickness I’m sure they don’t have great shielding. However I don’t hear any noise coming from them so far and they are running next to power cords. So far so good.
